<h3>How to Determine Your Target Ratio</h3>
<p>The best approach is competitive analysis. Check the anchor text distribution of the top 3 pages ranking for your target keyword. Use Ahrefs, Semrush, or Moz to export their backlink anchors. Match their distribution pattern.</p>
<p>If the top-ranking page for "content marketing strategy" has 45% branded anchors, 20% partial match, and 3% exact match, that is your benchmark. Over-indexing on exact match relative to your competitors is the fastest way to trigger a penalty.</p>
<h3>Internal Link Anchor Text Distribution</h3>
<p>Internal links follow different rules than external backlinks. <a href="https://www.seroundtable.com/google-no-internal-linking-overoptimization-penalty-27092.html">Google has confirmed</a> there is no internal linking over-optimization penalty. You can use more descriptive, keyword-rich anchors for internal links.</p>
